{"word":"ἐξαίνυμαι","slug":"ἐξαίνυμαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξαίνυμαι</b></el> <p/>epic <a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <i>to carry off</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>ἐξαίνυτο θυμὸν ἀμφοτέρω</el> <i>took away</i> life <i>from</i> both, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/>"}]}